The accident occurred in the Makgobaskloof mountains along the R71 between Tzaneen and Polokwane. JOHANNESBURG Twenty-nine police officers in Limpopo have sustained injuries after the bus they were travelling in lost control and overturned.The accident occurred in the Makgobaskloof mountains along the R71 between Tzaneen and Polokwane on Sunday afternoon.The department of transport and community safety s spokesperson Joshua Kwapa says there has been no fatality reported and the cause of the accident is being investigated. We can confirm that 29 police officers sustained injuries. So far there s not been any fatalities. (Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)